    <note>Sun(1) Dan(3) [21360] In tracing the lineage back to that of Sun(1) Quan [20609], first ruler of the San Guo Kingdom of Wu, Chen(1) Liang [3075] notes that Han had lost the 'Dao' and that the Cao(1) rulers of Wei were not legitimmate (zheng). Dan(3)'s son-in-law, imperial clansman, Zhao(1) Duanfu, may be the Wenzhou, Ruian county jinshi in 1226 (Zhejiang TZ, 127.15a) and this Duanfu may be a descendant of Shushao, first imperial clan jinshi [see SS(PRC), 234.7799]. But, there are many Duanfu listed in the genealogical tables and even a possible identification and inclusion in the dataset is two risky. Chen Liang, WJ, 27.8b-9a. CBD, 3, 1899.</note>
